# --- Build outputs -----------------------------------------------------------
**/target/
**/Cargo.lock

# --- Node-local on-disk state (the ONE store + ext-UI serve dir) ------------
# Repo-anchored under .cc-app/, same posture as lb's own .lb-dev and
# rubix-ai's .rubix-ai/. Threaded into BootConfig at the binary boundary
# (docs/WORKFLOW-LB.md §3, CLAUDE.md rule 5). NEVER committed.
.cc-app/
.cargo/config.toml

# --- zig toolchain cache ----------------------------------------------------
# The .cargo/config.toml redirects ZIG_LOCAL_CACHE_DIR to a writable
# scratch dir because /home/user/.cache/zig is bind-mounted read-only
# on this sandbox box (zig fails with "unable to create compilation:
# ReadOnlyFileSystem" otherwise). Two flavours land:
#   1. The root-relative `zig-cache/` (the `relative = true` form of
#      ZIG_LOCAL_CACHE_DIR — cwd at compile time).
#   2. Any other zig cache the toolchain creates (e.g. inside rust/target/).
# Always git-ignored — never committed.
**/zig-cache/
/zig-cache/

# --- Tooling noise -----------------------------------------------------------
**/*.swp
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/

# --- Node modules (pinned on disk; rebuilt from package.json via pnpm/npm) -
# `cargo build` / `cargo test` don't read this; the UI dev server installs
# on demand via `make setup` (pnpm install in ui/ + rust/extensions/care/ui/).
**/node_modules/
/ui/node_modules
/rust/extensions/care/ui/node_modules

# --- Stray `cargo` artifact dirs -------------------------------------------
# A typo'd invocation (`cargo build -p care/file` instead of `cargo build -p
# care`) sometimes drops a `file/` directory under the affected crate with
# a `tmp/` subdir (cargo's incremental-compilation scratch space). Same
# posture as `**/target/`: never committed.
**/file/tmp/
/rust/extensions/care/file/
# Playwright E2E artifacts (ui/)
ui/test-results/
ui/playwright-report/
